---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Explore China Handbook">
  <section class="section card" style="padding:28px;">
    <span class="pill">Handbook</span>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(34px,5vw,60px); margin-top:10px;">Explore China · Program Handbook</h1>
    <p class="muted" style="font-size:18px; max-width:860px;">
      This page presents the student-facing handbook content directly on-site.
      No external Figma/Notion links are required for participants.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section grid" style="grid-template-columns:1.2fr 1fr;">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>About this trip</h2>
      <p>
        We designed this route to feel like traveling with friends: immersive, social, and practical.
        You’ll see iconic places, but also experience daily city rhythm, food culture, and student exchange moments.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        Route: Shanghai → Suzhou → Hangzhou → Beijing · Duration: 10 days
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card" style="padding:0; overflow:hidden;">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1549692520-acc6669e2f0c?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80" alt="Shanghai skyline" style="height:100%; min-height:264px; width:100%; object-fit:cover; filter:saturate(0.88) contrast(0.96) brightness(1.02);" />
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>City Highlights</h2>
    <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);">
      <article class="card"><h3>Shanghai</h3><p class="muted">Yu Garden, The Bund, city walk, food and nightlife vibe.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3>Suzhou</h3><p class="muted">Museum, gardens, canal atmosphere, elegant Jiangnan style.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3>Hangzhou</h3><p class="muted">West Lake, Lingyin Temple, tea culture, relaxed scenic rhythm.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3>Beijing</h3><p class="muted">Great Wall, Forbidden City, Summer Palace, student social day.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Accommodation & Support</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="line-height:1.9; margin:0; padding-left:18px;">
      <li>Accommodation estimate: around ¥350/person/night in peak summer period</li>
      <li>Student-friendly rooming plan (final details in registration pack)</li>
      <li>Organizer support for coordination, logistics, and daily execution</li>
      <li>Language support and local guidance for key activities</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2>Food & Dietary Note</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      We focus on friendly, widely-loved dishes and do not force extreme food challenges.
      If you have dietary restrictions or allergies, tell us early and we’ll try to accommodate.
      Some venues may have limited substitutes depending on location.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card" style="margin-bottom:36px;">
    <h2>Application</h2>
    <p class="muted">Registration module placeholder. Replace this with your official form and timeline.</p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/trips/explore-china-2026-summer#register">Go to Trip Registration</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/">Back to Home</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
